</ul>
<h3>Introduction to stained glass</h3>
<p>June 28 from 1 pm to 5 pm<br>
Ages 16 and up<br>
Cost: $102.95 + tax (per person)<br>
<a href="https://anc.ca.apm.activecommunities.com/ottawa/activity/search/detail/131899?onlineSiteId=0&amp;locale=en-US&amp;from_original_cui=true">Enrollment opens: May 15 at 9 pm</a></p>
<p>Create your own stained-glass lantern with the guidance of an experienced artisan. In this workshop you’ll learn to cut and grind glass, construct a pattern, and solder your final design using copper foil. No previous experience is necessary—just enthusiasm to explore a new skill! Whether you’re inspired by the vibrant hues and intricate designs of stained-glass windows or looking to explore a new artistic avenue, all skill levels are welcome in this introductory workshop. Program supplies are included in the cost of registration. Light refreshments will be served.</p>
